-- Suzuki, Heck, Negishi Share Nobel Chemistry Prize for Palladium Catalysis
-- B y   T o b y   A l d e r
-- 2010-10-06T09:49:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/suzuki-heck-negishi-share-nobel-chemistry-prize-for-palladium-catalysis.html
Richard Heck from the U.S., and
Ei-ichi Negishi and Akira Suzuki, both from Japan, all shared
the 2010 Nobel Prize in Chemistry for “palladium-catalyzed
cross couplings in organic synthesis,” the Royal Swedish
Academy of Sciences said in a statement today in Stockholm.  All laureates will share the 10-million Swedish kronor
($1.5 million) prize, the Academy said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Toby Alder at 
 talder@bloomberg.net  